entry.title: Legal Advice and Assistance (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 1997
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Legal Advice and Assistance Regulations (Northern Ireland) 1981 so as to substitute a new scale of contributions payable for legal advice and assistance under Article 7(2) of the Legal Aid, Advice and Assistance (Northern Ireland) Order 1981.

entry.title: Valuation for Rating (Decapitalisation Rate) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 1997
entry.summary: These Regulations specify the percentage rate to be applied in relation to the notional cost of construction or provision or to the capital value of a hereditament where such a hereditament is valued by reference to the notional cost of constructing or providing it or to its capital value.

entry.title: The Borough of Blackpool (Electoral Changes) Order 1997
entry.summary: This Order gives effect to recommendations by the Local Government Commission for England for electoral changes in the borough of Blackpool. All of the existing wards of the borough are abolished and 22 new wards are created, having the names set out in the Schedule. Each new ward has two councillors. The areas of the new wards are demarcated on the map referred to in article 1(2). Prints of the map may be inspected at all reasonable times at the offices of the Blackpool Borough Council and at the offices of the Secretary of State for the Environment which, until May 1997, are located at 2 Marsham Street, London SW1P 3EB and, thereafter, at 2nd Floor, Ashdown House, 123 Victoria Street, London SW1E 6DE.

entry.title: The Criminal Justice Act 1967 (Application to Courts-Martial) (Evidence) Regulations 1997
entry.summary: These Regulations, which come into force on 1st April 1997, prescribe modifications to sections 9, 10 and 11 of the Criminal Justice Act 1967 (c. 80) in their application to courts-martial.

entry.title: Licensing (Register of Licences) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 1997
entry.summary: These regulations prescribe the form of the register of licences for the sale of intoxicating liquor by retail, kept by each clerk of petty sessions, for premises situated in the petty sessions district for which he acts.

entry.title: The Lloyd’s Underwriters (Double Taxation Relief) Regulations 1997
entry.summary: These Regulations make provision for the application of double taxation relief in relation to the income tax liability of an individual who is a member of Lloyd’s in respect of the profits or losses of his underwriting business.
